We are determined to continue progress with rebalancingof global demand, which requires internal rebalancing throughstructural reforms and exchange rate flexibility. We reiterateour commitments to move more rapidly toward moremarket-determined exchange rate systems and exchange rateflexibility to reflect underlying fundamentals and avoidpersistent exchange-rate misalignments. We will refrain fromcompetitive devaluation and will not target our exchange ratesfor competitive purposes. We will resist all forms ofprotectionism and keep our markets open. Large surplus economiesshould consider taking further steps to boost domestic sourcesof growth, while deficit economies should implement measures toimprove competitiveness.
